<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-12-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-12-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.612 Oranges/Spain/—: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moore</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-09T23:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">December 9,
                                        1925—11 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 9—8:15
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>76. Has the Department of Agriculture placed an embargo on Spanish
                            oranges? An immediate answer is vital to every American business
                            interest in Spain.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>